CATALLA DISADVOCATA, 198. Chattels disavowed or disowned3 as in case a man be indicted for theft of goods that are really his own property, which are produced against him as mainour, and which he disowns when demanded concerning them, such goods are forfeited. Goods found in the possession of a thies and disowned by him, which are omitted from the indictment‚ are similarly forfeited. If a man stole goods and killed himself before he was attainted thereos, he forfeited the goods stolen as well as his own: the stolen goods being apparently considered disavowed chattels.
